Free Lunches Starting in Sept. through December - Due to the recent USDA announcement, all students will be provided free meals through the end of December. All meals are now free for onsite, remote students, and any others that are ages 1-18. Remote students and those not enrolled will need to sign up with their schools/school where they live. It will be 1 day a week distribution on the first day of the week each week. Families will need to commit for the entire month. ONLY OFFSITE STUDENTS NEED TO FILL OUT THE REQUEST FORM!!!!! Please click the link to request offsite lunches for the month. Thank you

post_text:
Good Afternoon:
I hope you are spending some quality time with your families on this beautiful Sunday. This message is to provide a few updates about our current re-entry plan. Our plan was approved on July 22nd and the next morning ISBE came out with a new 130 page document. Although it didn’t appear to change our document too much there were a few items worth noting before registration begins on Monday. 1. Everyone will have access to extracurricular if they choose In-person or Remote
2. We are finalizing our Remote Learning Plan 2.0 plan with the union on July 27th and the guidelines will be posted in the re-entry plan for your review in order to make the best decision for your family.
Please remember that recommendations are changing almost daily and the plan may be adjusted prior to the start of school. Please be patient as we navigate through this new 130 page ISBE document. Thank you….And Remember, It’s A Great Day To Be A Timberwolf.
#twolves7pride

post_text:
Last week, the Illinois State Board of Education released their 2020 - 2021 guidance on returning to learn. The guidance encourages school districts to have students back in the classroom provided that we are in compliance with Illinois Department of Public Health Guidelines. This survey is designed to allow us to collect feedback from our community so that the administrative team and our staff can develop our return to school plan for this school year. Please keep in mind that all guidance and plans are continuing to change. Please take some time to day and fill out our survey. Thank you! #twolve7pride
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe4XPQNCphST3DrDSaQm16D-KtSV5Pg2VBbxaw5nTklLwoQRA/viewform?usp=sf_link

Free Meals for Midland Community Children (Ages 1-18)
- What: Grab and Go Sacks with Breakfast
- When: 11am to 1pm – As long as we are closed from student attendance at Midland CUSD #7 (M-F)
- Where: Any Midland school - curbside pickup. If you are not already on the daily meal list please call the school closest to you and let them know you wish to pick up a meal each day. Additionally, if you have a transportation concern, please let the school know that as well.
Midland High School- 309-463-2095
Midland Elementary School- 309-246-2775
Midland Middle School- 309-469-3131
- Who: Any student in the community. (Ages 1-18)
As with everything associated with this event, there are many unknowns that can’t be addressed until we get more information. We will adjust as needed.
Please note: If you know of any student needing meals during this time contact the school through any means. We will coordinate our resources to take care of them. We will get through this together.
#twolves7pride

post_text:
Dear Midland Community,

The Midland community has suffered a great loss this past weekend. It is with deep regret that we inform you of the passing of our superintendent, Mr. Bill Wrenn. On behalf of Midland schools, we offer our deepest condolences to the Wrenn family, friends, and the entire Midland community. Mr. Wrenn has lead the Midland school district for the last 4 years and will be sorely missed. Any school employee or Midland student needing support, our crisis support team members will be represented within the district this entire week.
text:
Dear Midland Community,

The Midland community has suffered a great loss this past weekend. It is with deep regret that we inform you of the passing of our superintendent, Mr. Bill Wrenn. On behalf of Midland schools, we offer our deepest condolences to the Wrenn family, friends, and the entire Midland community. Mr. Wrenn has lead the Midland school district for the last 4 years and will be sorely missed. Any school employee or Midland student needing support, our crisis support team members will be represented within the district this entire week.
